Four people were killed and three critically injured when a taxi collided with a car on the N4 near Solomon Mahlangu drive in Pretoria yesterday afternoon.Paramedics declared two men and two women dead at the scene, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said.A helicopter was used to airlift one of the inured, a child, to a trauma unit in Johannesburg.With heavy traffic as a result of the accident, motorists were advised to use alternative routes.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/four-killed-in-pretoria-smash-motorists-advised-to-use-alternative-routes-20170106